rComments: The lectures are all over the place, do not take this class unless you seek long morning lectures with a fake sense of exuberance that reads more often then not as performative and inauthentic. Further to that, the texts do not connect with lecture and lectures are oddly focus on specifics while claiming to illuminate the broad(which is never done)

I had him for a seminar, and although he's a nice guy, I didn't like him too much as a professor. There were good days, but on the most part he talks to much with too many pauses making you want to fall asleep
Gives creative and stimulating lectures that keep your interest in the course motivated. His passion rubs off for the better. You definitely get a challenging work load though.
Amazing lecturer, incredibly helpful and constructive. By far the best history prof I've had in four years at U of T.

Cohen's awesome to listen to, he speaks a split second faster then he thinks so often gets ahead of himself only to catch up to himself with some wicked word or hilarious point. Awesome, funny prof who is certainly organized and interesting, take 457

Hi Paul Cohen i am one of ur students and i think u r doing a masterful job. Your lectures are orgasmic, u seem very passioante about your work. When i become a professor i want to be just like u. Your the best
